President Trump addressed the issue of trade agreement violations and abuses during a visit to Ames Companies, Inc. in Pennsylvania. He signed two orders aimed at identifying and ending these abuses, and also established the Office of Trade and Manufacturing Policy within the White House. The President emphasized his commitment to bringing back American jobs, wealth, and dreams, and highlighted the positive impact his administration has already made in creating new manufacturing and construction jobs. The President thanked Secretary of Commerce Wilbur Ross and Peter Navarro for their efforts in addressing trade abuse.